5000|$|Behentrimonium chloride, {{also known}} as <b>docosyltrimethylammonium</b> <b>chloride</b> or BTAC-228, is a yellow waxlike organic {{compound}} with chemical formula 3(2)21 (...) (3)3, used as an antistatic agent and, sometimes, a disinfectant. It is commonly found in cosmetics such as conditioners, hair dye, and mousse, and also in detergents. Laboratory tests have indicated {{that it does not}} readily biodegrade.|$|E

